{"questionId":"9070042","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Consider the following lipid and carbohydrate.</p>\n<p><img src=\"__IMG__/cca48980342b30d0028be31365edbda3cda44770.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>In order to determine the number of carbon-carbon double bonds in a molecule of&nbsp;linoleic acid, 1.24 g of the lipid were dissolved in 10.0 cm<sup>3</sup> of non-polar solvent.</p>\n<p>The solution was titrated with a 0.300 mol dm<sup>–3</sup> solution of iodine, I<sub>2</sub>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Calculate the volume of iodine solution used to reach the end-point.&nbsp;</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>«<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{1.24\\,{\\text{g}}}}{{280.50\\,{\\text{g}}\\,{\\text{mo}}{{\\text{l}}^{ - 1}}}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>1.24</mn>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>g</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>280.50</mn>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>g</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>mo</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>l</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mo>−</mo>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span> =» 0.00442 «mol»</p>\n<p>0.00884 mol of C=C</p>\n<p><em><strong>OR</strong></em></p>\n<p>ratio of linoleic acid : iodine&nbsp;= 1:2</p>\n<p>«volume of I<sub>2</sub> solution&nbsp;=&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{0.00884\\,{\\text{mol}}}}{{0.300\\,{\\text{mol}}\\,{\\text{d}}{{\\text{m}}^{ - 3}}}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>0.00884</mn>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>mol</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>0.300</mn>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>mol</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>d</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>m</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mo>−</mo>\n            <mn>3</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span> =» 0.0295 «dm<sup>3</sup>» / 29.5 «cm<sup>3</sup>»</p>\n<p><em>Award <strong>[3]</strong> for correct final answer.</em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9070042","referenceCode":"17N.3.sl.TZ0.b.ii","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Calculate the volume of iodine solution used to reach the end-point.","paper":"3","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Options","Options","B: Biochemistry","B.3 Lipids","Options","B: Biochemistry"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}